        "ucagnn-cagra-ablation": {
            "description": "Separate systems ablation for CAGRA rather than the default U-CaGNN accuracy search. This space tests whether ANN graph augmentation or evaluation candidate prefiltering improves the validation CRRU trade-off. Keep full-catalog formal evaluation (`cagra_candidate_k=0`) as the baseline row; nonzero `cagra_candidate_k` changes candidate coverage and must be reported as an ANN retrieval/runtime ablation, not as the default ranking protocol. This space uses the same fixed early-stopping policy as the core search but a lower epoch cap because CAGRA trials add systems overhead.",
